title: High Antiretroviral Therapy Coverage
description: In 2022, Eswatini achieved a 95% coverage rate for antiretroviral therapy among people living with HIV, showcasing a strong healthcare response to the epidemic.

title: High Prevalence of HIV
description: As of 2022, 25.9% of Eswatini's population aged 15-49 is living with HIV, indicating a significant public health challenge.

title: Significant Merchandise Exports to Sub-Saharan Africa
description: In 2023, 90.44% of Eswatini's merchandise exports were directed to low- and middle-income economies in Sub-Saharan Africa, highlighting strong regional trade ties.

title: High Unemployment Rate
description: The unemployment rate in Eswatini was 34.4% in 2024, according to ILO estimates, reflecting economic challenges in job creation.

title: Low Total Fisheries Production
description: In 2022, Eswatini's total fisheries production was only 165 metric tons, indicating limited activity in this sector.

title: Low Incidence of Child Marriage
description: Only 0.1% of women aged 20-24 were married by age 15 in 2022, reflecting progress in reducing early marriages.

title: High Suicide Mortality Rate Among Males
description: In 2021, the suicide mortality rate for males in Eswatini was 45 per 100,000, indicating a critical mental health issue.

title: High Unemployment Among Educated Males
description: In 2021, 77.067% of males with intermediate education were unemployed, highlighting a mismatch between education and job opportunities.
